## ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
## .env — CIT Document Tracker Environment Configuration
## CIT Document Tracker - Group 6
##
## Copy this file to .env and fill in your values.
## NEVER commit the actual .env file to version control.
## ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

## MongoDB connection string
MONGO_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/cit_doctracker

## JWT secret — use a long random string in production
## Example: openssl rand -hex 32
JWT_SECRET=cit_group6_secret_key_2024
JWT_EXPIRES=7d

## Server port
PORT=3000

## ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## PRODUCTION BASE URL (CRITICAL FOR QR CODES)
## ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## Set this to the full public URL of your deployed app.
## This is used when generating QR codes for documents and events.
## QR codes will contain localhost URLs if this is not set.
##
## For Render.com deployments:
##   APP_BASE_URL=https://your-app-name.onrender.com
##
## For custom domain:
##   APP_BASE_URL=https://yourdomain.com
##
## Note: The backend also checks RENDER_EXTERNAL_URL (auto-set by
## Render) as a fallback, so on Render you only need this if you
## have a custom domain.
APP_BASE_URL=https://your-app-name.onrender.com
